I plan to try again on Saturday. The weather doesn't look good now, but it's only Monday today.
It seems that the challenge in this area has begun to show itself. Due to the FAA's stance on certain medications, I may have a hard time getting a medical certification.
This is not impossible, but it will take a lot of time and a lot of extra work.
Although this is a bit discouraging, it's only another problem to be solved, and it currently looks like it can be solved. It just takes a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I'll be facing next:
The FAA does not like ADHD. If you are taking medication for ADHD, you will definitely not pass the medical examination.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
